  "prompt": "How much sugar is good for health?",
  "response": "According to health experts, recommended daily sugar intake varies:\n\n1. American Heart Association guidelines:\n- Men: No more than 36 grams (9 teaspoons) per day\n- Women: No more than 25 grams (6 teaspoons) per day\n\n2. World Health Organization recommendation:\n- Less than 10% of total daily calories from added sugars\n- Ideally, less than 5% for additional health benefits\n\n3. Types of sugar to limit:\n- Added sugars\n- Processed/refined sugars\n- Sugary drinks\n- Desserts and candies\n\n4. Healthier alternatives:\n- Natural sugars from fruits\n- Complex carbohydrates\n- Whole foods\n- Moderate honey or maple syrup intake\n\n5. Health risks of excessive sugar:\n- Obesity\n- Type 2 diabetes\n- Heart disease\n- Tooth decay\n- Inflammation\n\nRemember, these are general guidelines, and individual needs may vary based on age, weight, activity level, and overall health. Consulting a healthcare professional for personalized advice is recommended.",
